      "text": "# Early life"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "78d5aee8859a4f4c0b41110fcc08a379",
      "text": "Stallman was born to Alice Lippman, a school teacher, and Daniel Stallman, a printing press broker, in 1953 in New York City. He was interested in computers at a young age; when Stallman was a pre-teen at a summer camp, he read manuals for the IBM 7094 ([[IBM 7090#IBM 7094]]) - [http://mgross.com/writing/books/the-more-things-change/bonus-chapters/richard-stallman-high-school-misfit-symbol-of-free-software-macarthur-certified-genius/ mgross.com] "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "296ada255affb565",
      "text": "From 1967 to 1969, Stallman attended a Columbia University Saturday program for high school students."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9c3e78da06926c4d",
      "text": "Stallman was also a volunteer laboratory assistant in the [[biology]] department at [[Rockefeller University]]. Although he was interested in mathematics and [[physics]], his teaching professor at Rockefeller thought he showed promise as a biologist."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d62d0fb46ec1836f9aae853d83d63c86",
      "text": "His first experience with actual computers was at the [[IBM New York Scientific Center]] when he was in high school. He was hired for the summer in 1970, following his senior year of high school, to write a numerical analysis program in [[Fortran]]."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "8f1d84c1e5e9c3ed",
      "text": "He completed the task after a couple of weeks, to which he said:"
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "id": "78ef85575ec3d293",
      "text": "<blockquote>I swore that I would never use FORTRAN again because I despised it as a language compared with other languages</blockquote>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "298ea7a9ce20c526",
      "text": "and spent the rest of the summer writing a text editor in [[APL]] and a [[preprocessor]] for the [[PL/I]] programming language on the [[IBM System/360]]."
    },
