    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "fb316ac094258db8c8a773358d857217",
      "text": "In response to Apple ([[Apple Inc]])'s Macintosh ([[Apple Macintosh]]) [[look and feel]] lawsuits against [[Microsoft]] and [[Hewlett-Packard]] in 1988, Stallman called for a boycott of Apple products on the grounds that a successful look-and-feel lawsuit would \"put an end to free software that could substitute for commercial software\".[https://www.gnu.org/bulletins/bull5.html#SEC9 GNU's Bulletin, vol. 1 no. 5 - GNU Project - Free Software Foundation] The boycott was lifted in 1995, which meant the FSF started to accept patches ([[patch (computing)]]) to GNU software for Apple operating systems.[https://www.gnu.org/bulletins/bull18.html#SEC13 GNU's Bulletin, vol. 1 no. 18 - GNU Project - Free Software Foundation]"
    },
