        "id": "b1390c8e9ad35eb3",
        "site": "law.commons.world",
        "slug": "copyright-reduction",
        "title": "Copyright Reduction",
        "text": "Stallman has regularly given a talk entitled \"Copyright vs. Community\" where he reviews the state of DRM and names many of the products and corporations which he boycotts. "
      },
      "id": "b1390c8e9ad35eb3",
      "type": "add",
      "date": 1457782637419
    },
    {
      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "570bda2d62fa6f147e724b792bf6343e",
        "text": "Richard Matthew Stallman (born March 16, 1953), often known by his initials, rms, is a software freedom activist and computer programmer. He campaigns for software to be distributed in a manner such that its users receive the freedoms to use, study, distribute and modify that software. Software that ensures these freedoms is termed free software. Stallman launched the GNU Project, founded the Free Software Foundation, developed the GNU Compiler Collection and GNU Emacs, and wrote the GNU General Public License - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Stallman wikipedia]"
      },
      "id": "570bda2d62fa6f147e724b792bf6343e",
      "date": 1457782638748
    },
    {
      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "0865584f7eb18b96cbd3b22120711deb",
        "text": "Stallman launched the GNU Project in September 1983 to create a Unix-like computer operating system composed entirely of free software. With this, he also launched the free software movement. He has been the GNU project's lead architect and organizer, and developed a number of pieces of widely used GNU software including, among others, the GNU Compiler Collection, the GNU Debugger and the GNU Emacs text editor. In October 1985 he founded the Free Software Foundation."
      },
      "after": "570bda2d62fa6f147e724b792bf6343e",
      "id": "0865584f7eb18b96cbd3b22120711deb",
      "date": 1457782641960
    },
    {
      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "2ee5e9b3ab38b42879876fbed56652a3",
        "text": "Stallman pioneered the concept of copyleft, which uses the principles of copyright law to preserve the right to use, modify and distribute free software, and is the main author of free software licenses which describe those terms, most notably the GNU General Public License (GPL), the most widely used free software license."
      },
      "after": "0865584f7eb18b96cbd3b22120711deb",
